ce:section.ce:para:
To evaluate the role of imprinting effect on nanosensor performance, MIP/CQD/SPCE, and NIP/CQD/SPCE were prepared and tested by analytical curve (Fig. 8
                        B and C). The determination of PMX at different concentrations was performed by DPV (Table 1
                        ) under the optimal conditions. The response of the MIP and NIP nanosensor were obtained using DPV measurements in redox marker solution after rebinding of PMX with several concentrations. The results show that MIP film demonstrated better adsorption ability than the NIP film.
